00:00:02.220 --> 00:00:03.520
Welcome to Instant Cooking

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:06.760
Today we are making Roti Poha

00:00:07.360 --> 00:00:13.880
For this you need 5-6 Rotis, Chapatis, or Tortilla coarsely grind in a grinder.

00:00:14.260 --> 00:00:17.880
or grind by using your hand your finger

00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:25.180
After grinding the chapatis take a pan. Add 1 -1/2 tsp of Olive oil

00:00:25.880 --> 00:00:28.760
Normal refined oil, spread all over the pan

00:00:30.120 --> 00:00:33.100
Now add 1tsp of cumin seeds

00:00:34.100 --> 00:00:36.660
cook till cumin seeds change it colour

00:00:39.320 --> 00:00:42.100
now add 2 clove of chopped garlic

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:46.500
and 1/82 inch of very finely chopped ginger

00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:48.920
cook it for couple of second

00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:54.400
and then add 5-6 curry leaves

00:00:58.460 --> 00:01:01.720
now add 4 chopped green chilly

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:07.940
if you don't want your poha very hot then avoid green chilly

00:01:08.940 --> 00:01:13.580
after adding green chilly add 2 finely chopped onion

00:01:14.200 --> 00:01:16.520
2 medium size finely chopped onion

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:22.980
and cook till onion is transparent

00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:29.960
Now add 1/4 tsp of turmeric

00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:35.520
1/2 tsp of coriander powder &amp; 1/2 tsp of garam masala

00:01:35.980 --> 00:01:38.860
mix it well and cook it for couple of seconds

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:41.800
and now add 1 finely chopped tomatoes

00:01:42.260 --> 00:01:44.880
and cook if for 1/2 a minute

00:01:48.680 --> 00:01:51.600
Add salt to taste and sauted it

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:00.640
and now add our crushed roti and mix it well

00:02:06.300 --> 00:02:08.060
and cook it for 2 mins.

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:15.160
till all the masala are absorbed by the grind chapati

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:19.280
now garnish with coriander leaves

00:02:21.740 --> 00:02:22.860
and serve it

